# NOT EXECUTABLE — parked follow-up slice (slice 2). The .feature.draft suffix
# keeps these scenarios out of every *.feature glob and the acceptance runner
# (specs/pipeline/runtime.js), so they cannot hard-fail the hardener's gate before
# their step handlers exist (BL-233 slice-scoping). Promote each scenario into the
# live BL-425 .feature file only when slice 2 is actually built, with its step
# handlers in the same parcel.
#
# Slice 2 — NON-DISRUPTIVE QUESTION MODE (the /btw-motivated path; the human's
# emphasised ask). Slice 1 is the disruptive REDIRECT (interrupting pane inject).
# Slice 2 adds the DEFAULT mode: a plain (un-marked) message in a role's topic is a
# QUESTION — the agent is NOT pulled off its task; it is handed the question as a
# mailbox NOTE it dequeues at its next natural break (when it finishes its current
# task), answers, and posts the answer BACK into that role's topic. Only the ANSWER
# reaches the topic, never the agent's ordinary activity — structural, because BAU
# never runs the reply command the note instructs. /btw itself is NOT used: it is a
# read-only side question whose answer lands in an ephemeral overlay with no tool
# access, so it cannot round-trip to the phone (see the ticket's /btw investigation).
# Mode selector: default = question; a leading `!` marks a redirect (slice 1).

Feature: a plain Telegram message asks an agent a question without disturbing it, and the answer comes back

  Background:
    Given a running swarm with per-agent Telegram topics and the authorised human

  # BL-425 question-is-queued-not-interrupting-06
  Scenario: a plain message in a role's topic is queued to that role, not injected into its pane
    Given the "coder" role is mid-task and the authorised human posts a plain message in the coder topic
    When the message is handled
    Then it is delivered to the coder role as a mailbox note and the coder's pane is not interrupted

  # BL-425 question-answer-returns-to-topic-07
  Scenario: an agent answers a queued question back into its own topic at its next break
    Given the "coder" role has a queued human-question note carrying the coder topic id
    When the coder role finishes its current task and answers the note
    Then the answer is posted back into the coder topic

  # BL-425 question-excludes-bau-08
  Scenario: an agent's ordinary activity is not posted to its topic
    Given the "coder" role is doing ordinary pipeline work with no queued human question
    When the coder role produces its normal pane activity
    Then nothing is posted to the coder topic

  # BL-425 mode-selector-marker-picks-redirect-09
  Scenario Outline: the leading marker chooses redirect versus question
    Given the authorised human posts "<message>" in the coder topic
    When the message is handled
    Then it is treated as a "<mode>"

    Examples:
      | message                    | mode     |
      | !stop and fix the lint     | redirect |
      | what are you working on?   | question |
